VS angeetha Ksheerasagaram introduced two pairs of sisters in two different concerts at Thyagaraya Ganasabha Mini auditorium. The two pair were accompanied by Kolanka Sai Kumar on the violin and Ramakrishna on mridangam. The first concert was by the Skandagiri sisters: Ashrita and Amruta. Both the artistes combined well. They began with Kedaragowla varnam Samidaya in Adi talam. Rakshamam in Gambhiranata was their next number, well-presented in unison. Sabhapatiki in Abhogi of Gopalakrishna Bharati was presented later. After rendering Ninnuchuji Dhanyudaiti in Sourastra of Patnam Subramanya Iyer they took up Shanmukhapriya as their main essay. . Vaddane Varu of Thyagaraja in this was done with thoughtful nereval and brisk swarakalpana. They concluded their show with a composition of Annamacharya's: Vatti Mopu in Salagabhairavi ragam.Kaveri and Saraswathi, the second pair of sisters, opened with Thodi varnam Era Napai, and went for Ninne Bhajanaseyuvada of Thyagaraja in Nata. Later they chose to present a GNB composition Saraswathi Namostuthe in Saraswathi. After rendering Anupama Gunambudhi in Athana in Khandachapu talam, the pair went for the main essay of their concert, Poorvikalyani. The raga presentation was neat and precise. Meenakshime Mudam Dehi was their choice number in this. .
